# NextFlow - Cursor IDE Rules

## Project Overview
NextFlow is a pixel-perfect Krea.ai UI clone for LLM workflows.
Stack: Next.js 14, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, React Flow, Zustand, Prisma, Trigger.dev, Clerk.

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode always. No any types - use unknown and type guards.
- Use named exports (not default) for components, except page.tsx files.
- File naming: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utilities, kebab-case for routes.
- Always destructure props with typed interface.
- Use const over let. Never var.

## React & Next.js
- App Router ONLY. No pages/ directory.
- Server Components by default. Add "use client" only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs).
- API routes use Next.js Route Handlers (not pages/api).
- Use React.FC<Props> typing for all components.
- Never use useEffect for data fetching - use Server Components or SWR.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only. No CSS-in-JS, no styled-components.
- Dark theme: bg-[#0A0A0A] app, bg-[#111111] panels, border-[#222222] borders.
- Accent: text-violet-500, bg-violet-500, border-violet-500.
- Use cn() helper (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes.
- Responsive: mobile-first but canvas is desktop-optimized.

## State Management
- Zustand for all client state (nodes, edges, history).
- No Redux, no Context API for global state.
- Keep stores in src/store/ directory.
- Use immer-style updates with set().

## Database
- ALL database access through Prisma only.
- Auth: always verify userId from Clerk before any DB operation.
- Use prisma.workflow.findFirst({ where: { id, userId } }) - never trust client-provided IDs alone.

## Trigger.dev
- ALL async node execution MUST be Trigger.dev tasks. Never call external APIs directly from route handlers for node execution.
- Task IDs must be kebab-case: "llm-execute", "crop-image", "extract-frame".
- Always handle task errors and update NodeRun status in DB.

## Error Handling
- Use try/catch in all async functions.
- Return typed error responses from API routes: { error: string, code: string }.
- Show user-friendly error messages (not raw error strings).
- Log errors server-side, never expose stack traces to client.

## React Flow
- nodeTypes object must be defined OUTSIDE component to avoid re-registration.
- edgeTypes same rule.
- Always use useCallback for onConnect, onNodesChange, onEdgesChange handlers.
- Handle IDs must be unique within a node: ${nodeId}-${handleName}.

## Imports Order
1. React/Next.js imports
2. Third-party libraries
3. Internal components (absolute paths with @/)
4. Internal utilities/types
5. Relative imports (avoid when possible)

## What NOT to do
- Never use document.getElementById - use React refs.
- Never store sensitive keys in NEXT_PUBLIC_ env vars (only Clerk publishable key and Transloadit key are exceptions).
- Never make direct Gemini API calls from the frontend.
- Never skip Zod validation on API route inputs.
- Never render user-provided HTML without sanitization.
